Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at the National Building Museum in Washington, D.C. to celebrate the 75th anniversary of the State of Israel. She highlighted the enduring bond between the United States and Israel, emphasizing America's commitment to Israel's security and its unwavering support. Harris also expressed the administration's belief in promoting a more integrated and interconnected Middle East, building on Israel's peace treaties with Egypt, Jordan, the UAE, Bahrain, and Morocco. She reaffirmed the administration's commitment to a two-state solution for Israelis and Palestinians, as well as the fight against antisemitism. Harris praised Israel's innovation in science, technology, and medicine, particularly in areas such as water management and clean energy. She concluded by emphasizing the importance of continuing the work of strengthening the partnership between the United States and Israel in the years to come.